mpleting-a-historic-mission-around-the-moon-180988513/</guid></item><item><title>这些野生黑猩猩已经在“内战”中战斗了近十年。这是同类中最血腥的分裂</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-wild-chimps-have-been-fighting-in-a-civil-war-for-nearly-a-decade-its-the-bloodiest-split-ever-seen-among-their-kind-180988527/</link><description>乌干达的恩戈戈黑猩猩已经分裂成两个主要派系，自 2018 年分裂以来，已有数十人死亡。一项新的研究详细描述了前所未有的暴力行为，这可能有助于揭示人类战争的进化基础</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 20:12:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/these-wild-chimps-have-been-fighting-in-a-civil-war-for-nearly-a-decade-its-the-bloodiest-split-ever-seen-among-their-kind-180988527/</guid></item><item><title>这幅文森特·梵高的画被发现包裹在宜家袋子和血迹斑斑的枕头中。现在，这件艺术品已恢复昔日的辉煌</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-vincent-van-gogh-painting-was-found-wrapped-in-an-ikea-bag-and-a-blood-stained-pillow-now-the-artwork-has-been-restored-to-its-former-glory-180988530/</link><description>艺术侦探阿瑟·布兰德 (Arthur Brand) 于 2023 年找回了《春天的纽南牧师住宅花园》(The Parsonage Garden at Nuenen in Spring)，距其从荷兰博物馆被盗三年后。经过精心修复，画布现在重新展出</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 19:00:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-vincent-van-gogh-painting-was-found-wrapped-in-an-ikea-bag-and-a-blood-stained-pillow-now-the-artwork-has-been-restored-to-its-former-glory-180988530/</guid></item><item><title>经过近 80 年的怀疑，科学家称插在大象肋骨之间的矛提供了尼安德特人狩猎大型动物的证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-nearly-80-years-of-doubt-scientists-say-a-spear-lodged-between-elephant-ribs-offers-evidence-that-neanderthals-hunted-big-game-180988522/</link><description>1948年，业余考古学家发掘了这些遗骸，这应该改变了研究人员对尼安德特人的看法。但糟糕的记录在科学界引起了怀疑</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 16:05:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-nearly-80-years-of-doubt-scientists-say-a-spear-lodged-between-elephant-ribs-offers-evidence-that-neanderthals-hunted-big-game-180988522/</guid></item><item><title>这位时装设计师与萨尔瓦多·达利和让·谷克托合作，想象出美妙的超现实主义服装</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-surrealism-inspired-fashions-of-elsa-schiaparelli-take-the-spotlight-in-london-180988503/</link><description>维多利亚和阿尔伯特博物馆的新展览展示了夏帕瑞丽家族的历史和遗产，重点关注其创始人独特的创作过程</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 13:33:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/the-surrealism-inspired-fashions-of-elsa-schiaparelli-take-the-spotlight-in-london-180988503/</guid></item><item><title>随着南极栖息地的消失，帝企鹅现在被认为是濒临灭绝的物种</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/as-their-antarctic-habitat-melts-away-emperor-penguins-are-now-considered-an-endangered-species-180988520/</link><description>国际自然保护联盟预测，到 2080 年代，鸟类数量可能会减少一半。该组织还改变了南极海狗和南象海豹的地位</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 20:35:14 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/as-their-antarctic-habitat-melts-away-emperor-penguins-are-now-considered-an-endangered-species-180988520/</guid></item><item><title>章鱼的性行为变得更奇怪了。除了储存精子外，雄性的专门交配臂还可以“品尝”雌性激素</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/octopus-sex-just-got-weirder-in-addition-to-depositing-sperm-males-specialized-mating-arm-can-taste-female-hormones-180988500/</link><description>新研究表明，总胚轴既是生殖器官又是感觉器官，这在动物中是罕见的组合</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 18:38:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/octopus-sex-just-got-weirder-in-addition-to-depositing-sperm-males-specialized-mating-arm-can-taste-female-hormones-180988500/</guid></item><item><title>首次公开展示的神秘而具有纪念意义的卷轴描绘了印度殖民时期艺术融合的图景</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mysterious-monumental-scroll-public-display-first-time-aints-picture-artistic-fusion-colonial-india-180988512/</link><description>新展览分享了英国东印度公司几个世纪以来对东亚和东南亚影响力的艺术遗产</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 17:45:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/mysterious-monumental-scroll-public-display-first-time-aints-picture-artistic-fusion-colonial-india-180988512/</guid></item><item><title>耶稣的裹尸布还是中世纪的赝品？ DNA 证据使都灵裹尸布的争论进一步复杂化</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/jesus-burial-cloth-or-medieval-forgery-dna-evidence-further-complicates-the-debate-over-the-shroud-of-turin-180988514/</link><description>一项新的分析揭示了有争议的亚麻布上有各种植物、动物和人类的痕迹。但外部专家对这些发现表示怀疑，这可能会使识别裹尸布最初佩戴者的工作变得复杂</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:17:46 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/jesus-burial-cloth-or-medieval-forgery-dna-evidence-further-complicates-the-debate-over-the-shroud-of-turin-180988514/</guid></item><item><title>观看这些攀岩鱼在刚果盆地攀爬 50 英尺的瀑布，这是非洲这种行为的第一个已知证据</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/watch-these-rock-climbing-fish-scale-a-50-foot-waterfall-in-the-congo-basin-the-first-known-evidence-of-this-behavior-in-africa-180988502/</link><description>这种被称为贝类的小鱼利用鳍上微小的钩状生长物来上升，并且需要大量的休息。根据一项新的研究，完整的攀登可能需要大约十个小时</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 15:02:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/watch-these-rock-climbing-fish-scale-a-50-foot-waterfall-in-the-congo-basin-the-first-known-evidence-of-this-behavior-in-africa-180988502/</guid></item><item><title>啮齿动物小英雄留下了巨大的遗产。现在，柬埔寨为这只著名的嗅弹鼠建造了一座七英尺高的雕像</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-small-rodent-hero-left-a-giant-legacy-now-cambodia-honors-this-famous-bomb-sniffing-rat-with-a-seven-foot-statue-180988515/</link><description>非洲巨型袋鼠马加瓦在五年的职业生涯中清除了超过 150 万平方英尺的地雷，使他成为该国历史上最成功的嗅炸弹啮齿动物之一</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-small-rodent-hero-left-a-giant-legacy-now-cambodia-honors-this-famous-bomb-sniffing-rat-with-a-seven-foot-statue-180988515/</guid></item><item><title>新研究表明，早在机枪出现之前，古罗马军队就在庞贝城使用了这种有 2000 年历史的速射武器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/long-before-machine-guns-ancient-roman-troops-were-using-this-rapid-fire-weapon-180988504/</link><description>公元前 89 年，古罗马军队可能使用 Polybolos 平息了庞贝城的叛乱。这种独特的武器很可能是几个世纪前由一位希腊工程师开发的</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 11:13:28 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/long-before-machine-guns-ancient-roman-troops-were-using-this-rapid-fire-weapon-180988504/</guid></item><item><title>美国丢失的行李里面有什么？这些旅行者遗弃了一把武士刀、一颗陨石和一个有着神秘目的的机器人</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/whats-inside-americas-lost-luggage-these-travelers-abandoned-a-samurai-sword-a-meteorite-and-a-robot-with-a-mysterious-purpose-180988507/</link><description>无人认领的行李在阿拉巴马州一家占地 50,000 平方英尺的商店出售丢失的物品。年度报告探讨 2025 年物品包装如何反映文化趋势</description><pubDate>Thu, 09 Apr 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/whats-inside-americas-lost-luggage-these-travelers-abandoned-a-samurai-sword-a-meteorite-and-a-robot-with-a-mysterious-purpose-180988507/</guid></item><item><title>这块化石保持着已知最早章鱼的世界纪录。事实证明，它毕竟不是章鱼</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fossil-held-the-world-record-for-the-earliest-known-octopus-turns-out-its-not-an-octopus-after-all-180988511/</link><description>新研究表明，这个拥有 3 亿年历史的标本实际上是鹦鹉螺的亲戚</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 21:07:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-fossil-held-the-world-record-for-the-earliest-known-octopus-turns-out-its-not-an-octopus-after-all-180988511/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家没想到会在英格兰的这个遗址找到任何东西。然后，他们偶然发现了一座罗马别墅和一件被称为“诺福克尼斯湖水怪”的青铜器</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-didnt-expect-to-find-anything-at-this-site-in-england-then-they-stumbled-upon-a-roman-villa-and-a-bronze-artifact-dubbed-norfolk-nessie-180988505/</link><description>在英国东海岸开发风电场之前，沿着地下电缆路线进行的挖掘发现了一个拥有自己的浴室的古老农庄遗址</description><pubDate>Wed, 08 Apr 2026 17:47:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonian